body:
@sipa Thanks for fixing. Can you now also remove that line, as we don't need Boost chrono with Boost 1.52.
https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/bitcoin-qt.pro#L387

Edit: What is the main benefit of this pull, does it fix certain known issues with Windows or should it be faster? A few more details would be very nice. I'm currently doing an IBD with test- and mainnet.

@sipa : don't mind at all; I was lazy and didn't compile Qt libraries (or Bitcoin-Qt) on my Windows VM.

RE: leveldb port using a ton of disk space on Windows:  yes, saw that, it makes me want to cry...
I do now have a VM that can run the mingw gdb, so hopefully "we" can reproduce/fix it, but I'm not looking forward to learning about the details of how leveldb works to figure out what is broken.

